Gauteng Transport MEC, Jacob Mamabolo will visit survivors of the Pretoria bus fire today, at the Steve Biko academic hospital. Six people died in the flames on Friday. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Three separate investigations will be held into Friday's Moloto Road bus fire. It left six people dead. READ: Give us 6 months to fix roads - Mamabolo Gauteng Transport MEC, Jacob Mamabolo says the Gauteng provincial government, the SAPS and Putco bus services will all probe the incident. Earlier on Sunday, Mamabolo visited a survivor of the fire at the Steve Biko Academic Hospital. Mamabolo conveyed his condolences to the families of the deceased and sent messages of support to the people injured in the collision.